        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Date::MONTH_NAME can cause confuse in some languages. For example, in Finnish Zend_Date::MONTH_NAME evaluates to the conjugated form of the month name, \"January\" => \"tammikuuta\" (should be \"Tammikuu\"). I propose that Zend_Date::MONTH_NAME would be mapped to the \"stand-alone\" type month name instead of using \"format\" type month name of CLDR data. In CLDR xml-data this would be:\r\n\r\n{code:xml}\r\n<months>\r\n  <monthContext type=\"stand-alone\">\r\n    <monthWidth type=\"wide\">\r\n       ... (Zend_Date::MONTH_NAME)\r\n    <\/monthWidth>\r\n  <monthContext>\r\n<\/months>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nNote 1:\r\nTo make this change either 1) CLDR data should be normalized as there is no value for English \"stand-alone\" month name (ZF should have to wait this to be accomplished), 2) or Zend_Date will use \"format\" type name for languages with the same \"format\" and \"stand-alone\" type month names.\r\n\r\nNote 2:\r\nOf course we still need \"format\" type month names, which can be conjugated in some languages. For this I propose a new constant Zend_Date::MONTH_NAME_FORMAT.\r\n\r\n(Note 3: Atm. there is an issue in Finnish \"stand-alone\" month names in CLDR data. Those should start with the capitals.)"
        },
